30:58.490 --> 31:00.190
I'm not gonna lie about it.

31:00.192 --> 31:02.860
When I came to them,
I was still using drugs.

31:02.862 --> 31:05.295
Due respect to them,
and I went to kick.

31:05.297 --> 31:07.631
I've been straight since,
and I love ghetto brothers.

31:07.633 --> 31:10.067
There's a purpose here.

31:10.069 --> 31:12.870
It's something that's beneficial
to the neighborhood,

31:12.872 --> 31:14.905
the establishment,
and everybody else.

31:14.907 --> 31:17.407
Black Benji, Benjamin Cornell

31:17.409 --> 31:19.142
was introduced to me by Charlie.

31:19.144 --> 31:21.578
He said, "Benji wants to
check out the ghetto brothers."

31:21.580 --> 31:23.347
Sure.
I said, "would do you do?"

31:23.349 --> 31:25.115
He said, "I work as a drug
counselor."

31:25.117 --> 31:27.017
Said, "very good.
That's very good."

31:27.019 --> 31:29.119
So one day,
kids were in the program,

31:29.121 --> 31:31.154
and the ghetto brothers club,
I'm looking at them,

31:31.156 --> 31:33.490
and he sits down in a chair
and he's talking to kids,

31:33.492 --> 31:36.193
and I saw they were on the floor
telling them stories,

31:36.195 --> 31:39.229
and I looked,
I said, "that's wonderful."

31:39.231 --> 31:41.598
And then he talks to the older
people in my community.

31:41.600 --> 31:44.401
He said, "man, there's something
about this guy, I like that."

31:44.403 --> 31:46.303
Charlie, come here.

31:46.305 --> 31:48.939
I think we should
stop the warlords

31:48.941 --> 31:51.441
and put a peacemaker,
that's the man.

31:51.443 --> 31:53.343
"Let's make them into
a peace ambassador."

31:53.345 --> 31:55.245
He became the third staff
of the ghetto brothers.

31:55.247 --> 31:57.014
You're gonna be the ambassador
for peace.

32:00.018 --> 32:01.685
What I knew
about the ghetto brothers,

32:01.687 --> 32:05.222
the first thing was I heard
a lot about karate Charlie.

32:05.224 --> 32:06.690
Everybody kept
hearing about this guy

32:06.692 --> 32:08.425
karate Charlie, right?

32:08.427 --> 32:12.396
Guys in gangs, you had to have
a karate something.

32:12.398 --> 32:15.599
Like in this one gang,
you had a karate Kenny.

32:15.601 --> 32:19.269
I remember him.
Then you had a karate Joe nose.

32:19.271 --> 32:21.538
We had a guy named karate Moe,

32:21.540 --> 32:23.407
but it was all
because of everybody

32:23.409 --> 32:26.176
heard about this guy
named karate Charlie.

32:26.178 --> 32:28.312
The rep for him that we heard

32:28.314 --> 32:30.113
was that he was a bad dude.

32:30.115 --> 32:32.015
He was into karate and stuff.

32:32.017 --> 32:34.084
They were saying, Oh,
he knocked a guy out

32:34.086 --> 32:35.652
by kicking him in the head,

32:35.654 --> 32:38.355
and it was like
an urban legend almost.

32:38.357 --> 32:40.324
Charlie was a warrior.

32:40.326 --> 32:44.328
He lived like
the Japanese Bushido.

32:44.330 --> 32:46.630
You cross me,
you cross my honor?

32:46.632 --> 32:48.432
Yah! You're going down.

32:48.434 --> 32:52.336
Remember, I just came
out of the marine corps.

32:52.338 --> 32:56.273
So what I wanted
was a little marine corps.

32:56.275 --> 32:58.041
Because he brought
the military discipline

32:58.043 --> 32:59.409
to the ghetto brothers.

32:59.411 --> 33:01.078
The ghetto brothers
were not known for guns.

33:01.080 --> 33:02.579
We were known for the hands.

33:02.581 --> 33:04.448
Ghetto brothers were very good
with hands and legs.

33:04.450 --> 33:06.316
So Charlie was the instructor.

33:06.318 --> 33:11.688
They called me karate Charlie,
and they called the founder,

33:11.690 --> 33:15.025
Benji Melendez, the preacher.

33:15.027 --> 33:18.128
Charlie and I were brothers.
I mean, we were very close.

33:18.130 --> 33:19.763
But we were two worlds.

33:19.765 --> 33:25.202
Benji was a yin
while I was a Yang,

33:25.204 --> 33:28.071
black and white, soft and hard,

33:28.073 --> 33:31.274
rain and shine...
we were the opposites.

33:31.276 --> 33:34.277
The yin and Yang? That's true.
That's me and Charlie.

33:34.279 --> 33:36.246
Charlie was...

33:36.248 --> 33:38.248
and I would say, "no, Charlie."

33:38.250 --> 33:41.418
"Come on, Benjy!"
"No, Charlie, come on."

33:41.420 --> 33:43.587
Sometimes it was
the other way around, too.

33:43.589 --> 33:45.689
Charlie had to calm Benjy down.

33:45.691 --> 33:48.425
You know, they kept each other,
you know, at bay.

33:48.427 --> 33:51.661
Yellow Benji,
he was more of a peacemaker.

33:51.663 --> 33:55.132
He was also trying
to let people know,

33:55.134 --> 33:57.768
look, let's stop fighting
amongst ourselves

33:57.770 --> 34:00.037
'cause we're only hurting
each other.

34:00.039 --> 34:02.339
Let's fight the man.
Let's hurt him.

34:02.341 --> 34:04.408
The enemy around the Bronx now
at this very moment

34:04.410 --> 34:06.043
is the policeman.

34:06.045 --> 34:07.811
Yes, this is a warrior thing.
Yes, it is.

34:07.813 --> 34:09.813
And we're here to defend
our brothers and sisters

34:09.815 --> 34:11.648
against people like them.

34:11.650 --> 34:13.784
If you're gonna communicate,
communicate, man.

34:13.786 --> 34:15.719
If you're gonna strike us,
we're gonna strike back.

34:15.721 --> 34:17.754
Right on!

34:42.780 --> 34:45.081
<i>Beyond running the gang,
yellow Benjy</i>

34:45.083 --> 34:47.484
<i>was also the leader
of the ghetto brothers band,</i>

34:47.485 --> 34:51.521
<i>a unique and well-loved
rock and Latin funk outfit.</i>

34:51.523 --> 34:54.591
The band and the gang
were two separate entities.

34:54.592 --> 34:57.227
The talent was definitely there.

34:57.229 --> 35:00.630
It was definitely
a Latin flavor.

35:00.632 --> 35:03.333
It also showed
what clubs could do.

35:03.335 --> 35:05.535
If they took
a different direction.

35:13.145 --> 35:14.644
I tell my brothers, listen,

35:14.646 --> 35:16.279
I notice that when you
talk to people,

35:16.281 --> 35:17.781
some people will listen,
some people don't.

35:17.783 --> 35:19.883
But the idea of music,
my brothers and I,

35:19.885 --> 35:22.219
music caters to all type
of people.

35:22.221 --> 35:23.854
So If you want to get a message,

35:23.856 --> 35:26.623
why don't we put it into song,
watch them listen.

35:26.625 --> 35:29.292
Then when we play the music,
what we always wanted to say

35:29.294 --> 35:31.261
to them and you put it
behind guitars is,

35:31.263 --> 35:34.431
"yo, man, that's me, man.
I live that type of life.

35:34.433 --> 35:36.533
What would be that song for you,
my brother?"

35:36.535 --> 35:38.735
I remember a lot of bongos.

35:38.737 --> 35:41.738
I always, you know,
remember bongo music.

35:41.740 --> 35:44.307
If they were jamming
up the street, you know,

35:44.309 --> 35:45.842
up the hill,
you could hear the music.

35:45.844 --> 35:47.777
When we played music,
why don't we play

35:47.779 --> 35:50.747
a little rock here,
a little Latin here,

35:50.749 --> 35:52.782
a little soul over here?

35:52.784 --> 35:55.552
So you heard Beatles,
sly and the family stone,

35:55.554 --> 35:57.487
Santana, you heard all of that.

35:57.489 --> 35:59.456
So every Friday, the gangs knew

35:59.458 --> 36:01.625
that we had music and a message.

36:21.712 --> 36:25.649
<i>In 1971 despite all efforts
by social workers</i>

36:25.651 --> 36:27.651
<i>and specialized police units,</i>

36:27.653 --> 36:31.421
<i>gang violence had escalated
to a fever pitch,</i>

36:31.423 --> 36:34.291
<i>plunging the streets
into a state of continual war</i>

36:34.293 --> 36:37.627
<i>unlike anything the city
had ever experienced before.</i>

36:37.629 --> 36:40.697
Drugs was a big factor
in gangs going haywire,

36:40.699 --> 36:42.732
lust for power, lust for turf.

36:42.734 --> 36:45.802
The wars with street gangs
could start from something

36:45.804 --> 36:49.806
that could be just as silly
as stepping on somebody's boots.

36:49.808 --> 36:52.442
Wars could get started
just from a rumor.

36:52.444 --> 36:54.377
Territory was a big issue.

36:54.379 --> 36:56.813
I had heard of some dudes
just getting popped

36:56.815 --> 36:58.748
from running down
the wrong block.

36:58.750 --> 37:00.383
The garbage can is here.

37:00.385 --> 37:02.385
If you go past that garbage can,

37:02.387 --> 37:04.654
although It's the same block

37:04.656 --> 37:07.257
in the same neighborhood,
it could be a war.

37:07.259 --> 37:09.593
The devil's rebels
is fighting gang,

37:09.595 --> 37:12.329
and on this night,
they found their first victims

37:12.331 --> 37:14.431
outside a corner grocery store.

37:14.433 --> 37:16.633
What looks like child's play
is not.

37:16.635 --> 37:19.436
In the middle of all this,
a young man was stabbed.

37:19.438 --> 37:21.371
It was the thing
about conquering.

37:21.373 --> 37:24.241
You go to their turf,
beat the hell out of these guys,

37:24.243 --> 37:26.509
and come back again and again
until they were forced...

37:26.511 --> 37:29.646
either they break up
or become part of the majority.

37:29.648 --> 37:31.915
So they did it
through barbarian style,

37:31.917 --> 37:33.483
warrior, vikings.

37:33.485 --> 37:36.353
They tried to take over
one of my divisions.

37:36.355 --> 37:38.788
They didn't quite make it,
and we killed two of they guys.

37:38.790 --> 37:40.624
They tried to burn down
my clubhouse.

37:40.626 --> 37:43.693
We killed two of they guys,
and five of they guys rolled up

37:43.695 --> 37:45.428
on one of the savage nomads.

37:45.430 --> 37:47.731
Know what they told him?
"We gonna give you hell, baby.

37:47.733 --> 37:50.333
"We gonna give you hell."
And they didn't even kill him.

37:55.006 --> 37:56.640
There were big gang wars

37:56.642 --> 37:58.842
between the savage skulls,
black spades,

37:58.844 --> 38:01.278
between the savage skulls,
the bachelors.

38:01.280 --> 38:03.346
Back then,
nobody had cell phones,

38:03.348 --> 38:04.714
but It's like drums...
you hear it.

38:04.716 --> 38:06.616
You hear it all over the place.

38:06.618 --> 38:09.586
You know, one way or another,
you hear who's beating who.

38:09.588 --> 38:11.688
The violence was everywhere.

38:11.690 --> 38:13.523
You could see the fights
across the street.

38:13.525 --> 38:15.425
You could hear the shots
in the nighttime.

38:15.427 --> 38:17.527
What made life interesting
in the South Bronx

38:17.529 --> 38:21.298
for these young guys
was fighting, was killing.

38:21.300 --> 38:22.966
"Yo, I killed a dude today."
"What'd you do?"

38:22.968 --> 38:25.468
"I stabbed him in the throat.
What'd you do, man?"

38:25.470 --> 38:28.838
"Yo, I shot that dude."
"I burned this guy."

38:28.840 --> 38:31.374
You hear this,
and this is every day.

38:31.376 --> 38:32.609
It was a lawless time.

38:32.611 --> 38:34.611
If somebody got killed
on Hewitt place,

38:34.613 --> 38:36.513
their body stayed there.

38:36.515 --> 38:38.782
An ambulance wouldn't dare
come and pick that body up.

38:38.784 --> 38:41.051
The police came in riot gear
to take that body out there,

38:41.053 --> 38:42.919
and they didn't do
an investigation.

38:42.921 --> 38:44.454
They took that body out of there
as quick as possible

38:44.456 --> 38:45.588
because they didn't
want to get it.

38:45.590 --> 38:46.990
There's no ambulance coming.

38:46.992 --> 38:48.725
There are no ambulances,
all right?

38:48.727 --> 38:50.660
How long It's gonna take, man?

38:50.662 --> 38:53.863
The '70s when the drug trade
came in the city,

38:53.865 --> 38:57.067
that totally changed
the whole vibe on how we rumble.

38:57.069 --> 38:58.768
Now It's serious.

38:58.770 --> 39:00.837
Now we're gonna start
shooting at each other.

39:00.839 --> 39:03.640
In the '70s, you had firepower.

39:03.642 --> 39:05.975
You had some gangs
with arsenals.

39:05.977 --> 39:10.714
I've seen .357s.
I've seen 12-guage shotguns.

39:10.716 --> 39:12.749
I've seen dynamite
on the street.

39:12.751 --> 39:16.086
I've seen all this.
You'd be surprised, man.

39:16.088 --> 39:18.388
Pretty soon, they're gonna
steal the damn atom bomb.

39:24.562 --> 39:26.629
<i>As the bloodshed continued,</i>

39:26.631 --> 39:29.132
<i>the ghetto brothers worked
fervently to mediate peace</i>

39:29.134 --> 39:31.901
<i>amongst the ever-growing web
of turf battles.</i>

39:31.903 --> 39:34.771
A lot of things was happening
in the Bronx at the same time.

39:34.773 --> 39:37.073
We felt the whole world
was going through these changes.

39:37.075 --> 39:41.077
I said
this is getting out of hand.

39:41.079 --> 39:44.781
You know, we were pretty much
hurting fighting each other

39:44.783 --> 39:47.917
instead of going
against the real enemy.

39:47.919 --> 39:52.622
Benjy, he tried, man.
He tried to let us know that.

39:52.624 --> 39:55.425
They were like the club
that would be the mediators,

39:55.427 --> 39:57.994
you know, stopped a lot of us
from going out there

39:57.996 --> 40:00.663
and going ballistic on a whole
lot of wars, you know?

40:00.665 --> 40:03.466
I would sit down and reason
with a lot of these brothers.

40:03.468 --> 40:05.702
"Come here, guys.
Savage skulls, come here."

40:05.704 --> 40:08.505
"Savage nomads, come here.
Black spades, come over here."

40:08.507 --> 40:10.440
That's the way we used to talk.

40:10.442 --> 40:13.843
"It doesn't make any sense
with this turf thing, guys."

40:13.845 --> 40:18.181
It's us against the government.
It's not me against you.

40:18.183 --> 40:19.916
You are not hurting me.

40:19.918 --> 40:23.086
You're not the one
that's keeping me down.

40:23.088 --> 40:27.157
I don't have to fight you.
You're not the problem.

40:27.159 --> 40:28.892
"Yo, brothers, come on, man."

40:28.894 --> 40:30.727
"Nah,
but you don't understand, man!"

40:30.729 --> 40:32.695
He came into my turf
with his colors, man!

40:32.697 --> 40:34.664
"And he was just trying
to tell me..."

40:34.666 --> 40:37.000
because colors?

40:37.002 --> 40:39.002
Come on, guys,
think what I'm gonna say.

40:39.004 --> 40:41.938
Colors is gonna
make you go insane?

40:45.476 --> 40:48.111
<i>On December 8,
a series of events transpired</i>

40:48.113 --> 40:51.448
<i>that rocked the ghetto brothers
and the rest of the Bronx.</i>

40:51.450 --> 40:53.216
<i>As a result,
the outcome would come</i>

40:53.218 --> 40:56.152
<i>to change gang life
in New York City forever.</i>

40:56.154 --> 40:59.589
They came to the storefront
and said

40:59.591 --> 41:03.860
there was going to be a fight
at the bottom of the stairs.

41:03.862 --> 41:06.496
"Benjy, three gangs are coming
from Southern boulevard..."

41:06.498 --> 41:10.200
bongos, black spades,
and seven immortals.

41:10.202 --> 41:13.536
"They want to get
the Roman kings."

41:13.538 --> 41:18.741
Benji said, "let black Ben go,
Cornell go."

41:18.743 --> 41:20.944
"Benji, you got your job
cut out for you."

41:20.946 --> 41:22.879
You're gonna get me
the president, vice president,

41:22.881 --> 41:24.214
warlords of those three gangs.

41:24.216 --> 41:26.082
Bring them here
so we can broker a peace.

41:26.084 --> 41:28.618
"Bring them here, take some
ghetto brothers with you."

41:28.620 --> 41:29.886
So he left.

41:29.888 --> 41:31.988
He went with playboy

41:31.990 --> 41:34.924
and a few of the younger
ghetto brothers.

41:34.926 --> 41:37.660
We came down the stairs, right?

41:37.662 --> 41:38.862
And we stopped there,

41:38.864 --> 41:41.498
and there was about 13
to 20 of us.

41:41.500 --> 41:43.867
And then when we looked down,
we seen them,

41:43.869 --> 41:46.536
and you couldn't
even see the corner.

41:46.538 --> 41:49.672
That's how many there were,
and when we got to the bottom

41:49.674 --> 41:52.075
of the stairs
and they could've seen us,

41:52.077 --> 41:53.776
there was only about nine of us.

41:53.778 --> 41:56.179
That's when Benji came out,
and Benji said...

41:56.181 --> 41:58.848
he took a step forward,
and he said,

41:58.850 --> 42:01.684
"listen, brother,
we're here to talk peace."

42:01.686 --> 42:05.655
And the guy who came out,
he said, "peace, shit."

42:05.657 --> 42:07.524
That's when the guy
pull out the machete.

42:07.526 --> 42:09.626
That's when they had us
all surrounded.

42:09.628 --> 42:12.762
Benji said, "take, brother..."
Because there was too many.

42:12.764 --> 42:16.666
So I heard a noise,
you know, pow, like a slap,

42:16.668 --> 42:19.269
and Benji had got hit
in the stomach, and he tripped.

42:19.271 --> 42:23.573
At that time was a time
when they were killing,

42:23.575 --> 42:28.611
killing, killing, killing,
and Cornell wasn't recognized.

42:28.613 --> 42:30.880
They recognized violence,

42:30.882 --> 42:33.583
and they recognized somebody
that'd throw a punch.

42:45.596 --> 42:49.933
It was a moment in time
that could have been avoided.

42:49.935 --> 42:52.835
If I could just turn back
the hands of time,

42:52.837 --> 42:55.104
this wouldn't ever
have happened.

42:55.106 --> 42:57.774
And I looked at my brothers
today, my real brothers,

42:57.776 --> 43:00.910
Says, "think about it...
there was that fateful day"

43:00.912 --> 43:04.147
that I sent him
to bring peace."

43:04.149 --> 43:05.982
My brother looked at me, said,

43:05.984 --> 43:07.951
"Benji, but you didn't know
what was gonna..."

43:07.953 --> 43:09.986
"no, you're right, I didn't know
what was gonna happen."

43:09.988 --> 43:11.321
I didn't know the fate,

43:11.323 --> 43:14.924
"but it was my decision
to send him."

43:18.996 --> 43:20.730
That was one of the worst days

43:20.732 --> 43:23.166
in South Bronx history
when he got murdered.

43:23.168 --> 43:26.102
The word on the street was
he was trying to make peace,

43:26.104 --> 43:28.204
and he was murdered
trying to make peace,

43:28.206 --> 43:31.341
and basically after that,
the South Bronx,

43:31.343 --> 43:33.109
fort Apache was out of control.

43:33.111 --> 43:35.178
When this tragedy happened,

43:35.180 --> 43:38.247
they went to war and even got
many gangs to move

43:38.249 --> 43:40.717
against the seven immortals
and the black spades.

43:40.719 --> 43:45.755
Every gang in my neighborhood
at least were so mad

43:45.757 --> 43:47.123
that they killed this guy,

43:47.125 --> 43:48.858
they were running
through the streets.

43:48.860 --> 43:51.861
They were burning everything.
I mean, pandemonium hit.

43:51.863 --> 43:53.997
Black spades
wasn't gonna back down.

43:53.999 --> 43:56.032
If they was gonna
fully get attacked.

43:56.034 --> 43:58.101
Then there was the time when
the spade leaders,

43:58.103 --> 44:00.803
all of them said hell with it,
get ready for war.

44:00.805 --> 44:03.940
How rumors spread.
How news spread.

44:03.942 --> 44:07.043
There was not a gang
in the whole of New York

44:07.045 --> 44:08.845
that was not aware
what's happening.

44:08.847 --> 44:10.079
I put out a bulletin,

44:10.081 --> 44:12.682
and I started calling
ghetto brothers,

44:12.684 --> 44:14.817
all the ghetto brothers.

44:14.819 --> 44:17.687
Charlie wanted to get
the ghetto brothers

44:17.689 --> 44:19.055
to mobilize
for the biggest bloodbath

44:19.057 --> 44:20.757
in the history of New York.

44:20.759 --> 44:22.792
We lost a member,
they viciously murdered him

44:22.794 --> 44:23.860
out there in the street.

44:23.862 --> 44:25.795
Now It's an eye for an eye

44:25.797 --> 44:27.330
because another ghetto brother
loses a life,

44:27.332 --> 44:30.066
six of whoever,
whether they his kids,

44:30.068 --> 44:32.068
his mother, his father,
they lose their lives.

44:32.070 --> 44:34.804
Who was it that took
the lives of two of your...

44:34.806 --> 44:36.039
some dude out there.

44:36.041 --> 44:39.208
At the time, I was...
I was blind.

44:39.210 --> 44:41.878
And I said, no,
I'm gonna make everyone pay.

44:41.880 --> 44:45.748
That's when I said I'm going to
just start killing, you know?

44:45.750 --> 44:48.384
Watch. The sword is sharp.

44:48.386 --> 44:50.453
Look, razor-sharp.

44:50.455 --> 44:52.455
And Benji kept saying,
"but, Charlie,

